Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportVoltage(25.10)                                      reportVoltage(25.10)

Name
       reportVoltage  -  This  command  reports  the  voltage  for the net/pin
       (term)/inst in the specific view under a specific corner

Syntax
       reportVoltage

       [-help]

       [-early]

        [-inst <string>]

       [-late]

       [-net <string>]

       [-quiet]

       [-term <string>]

       [-view <string>]

       This command reports the voltage for the  net/pin  (term)/inst  in  the
       specific view under a specific corner.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each reportVoltage parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all its  parameters,  use  the  man
              command:

              man reportVoltage

       -early Specifies that the voltage is repoted in the early mode.

       -inst <string>
              Reports the specified instance's power domain, cell name, timing
              library, view, mode, power net, and voltage information.

       -late  Specifies that the voltage is reported in the late mode.

       -net <string>
              Specifies the net voltage (driver's pin voltage).

       -quiet Displays  only the pin voltage-related information without other
              additional unnecessary information to avoid huge log size.

       -term <string>
              Specifies the term voltage.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the analysis view.

Related Information
       For more information, see the Low Power  Design  chapter  of  the  User
       Guide.

